            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "<i>Re: Medication Opportunity - ALERT</i>",
                    "text_style": {
                        "fontName": "Times-New-Roman-bold",
                        "parent_style": "BiggerText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "Dear {provider_full_name},",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "Alohacare is committed to ensuring our members receive integrated and high-quality care. Our approach integrates the management of behavioral, pharmacy and physical health care benefits. We have implemented a Quality Improvement Program to collaborate and assist you in providing safe, appropriate, and cost-effective care to patients. As part of this program, drug utilization algorithms based on evidence-based guidelines are utilized to identify any potential medication-related concerns.",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "<b>This letter has been generated because we have identified a member-specific quality opportunity. Please review the information at the top of each page and the corresponding patient list to determine if a change in therapy can be made.</b>",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "A clinical pharmacist may contact you to schedule a consultation and explain how the information can be used to support your prescribing decisions and help reduce the risks of adverse effects. You may also request a personal consultation, provide feedback, or request additional data by contacting your dedicated pharmacist at 808-973-7418",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "All patients listed in this document have received a paid prescription with your national identification number (NPI) identified as the prescriber. Please be aware some of these patients may have received a prescription from you at a different site of service as this mailing is directed to the address primarily associated with your DEA.",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "The enclosed information is derived from pharmacy and medical claims data; however, additional claims paid by cash or other insurance will not be listed. If you receive information you believe to be inaccurate, please contact our toll-free number at 808-973-7418 and destroy the information in a confidential manner.",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "Sincerely,",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "signature": {
                    "height": 50,
                    "string": "Hanh Bannister",
                    "text_style": {
                        "fontName": "Lucida-Handwriting-normal",
